' exportdef regression: child's OWN source has no #ifdef on SYM_X or SYM_Y, so
' its preprocessedLines is identical across both parent contexts. The bug
' surfaces because compile_obj_blocks embeds grandchild bytes into THIS
' child's binary; the grandchild's bytes DO depend on the propagated symbol,
' so the cached child binary baked under SYM_X is wrong when reused under
' SYM_Y. v1.54.4's cache key (preprocessedLines + overrides + version + debug
' + format) misses this because none of those inputs see SYM_X / SYM_Y.
OBJ
  gc : "expdef_grandchild"

PUB run() : result
  result := gc.kind()
